<!-- views/faq.ejs -->

<%- include("partials/header", { title: "FAQ - Aquarium World" }) %>

<%- include("partials/navigation") %>

<main class="faq-page">

    <section class="faq-hero">
        <h1>Frequently Asked Questions</h1>
        <p>
            Find answers to common questions about visiting Aquarium World,
            our marine exhibits, tickets, and conservation activities.
        </p>
    </section>


    <section class="faq-container">

        <div class="faq-item">
            <h2>What are Aquarium World's opening times?</h2>
            <p>
                Aquarium World is open daily from 
                <strong>9:00 AM to 6:00 PM</strong>.
                Last admission is 5:00 PM.
            </p>
        </div>


        <div class="faq-item">
            <h2>Where is Aquarium World located?</h2>
            <p>
                Aquarium World is located in the heart of the city and is
                easily accessible by public transport, car, and walking routes.
            </p>
        </div>


        <div class="faq-item">
            <h2>How much are the entrance tickets?</h2>
            <p>
                Ticket prices vary depending on visitor type.
                We offer standard, child, student, and family tickets.
                Please check our ticket office for current prices.
            </p>
        </div>


        <div class="faq-item">
            <h2>Do I need to book tickets online?</h2>
            <p>
                Online booking is recommended, especially during weekends
                and school holidays. Tickets are also available at the entrance.
            </p>
        </div>


        <div class="faq-item">
            <h2>What marine zones can visitors explore?</h2>
            <p>
                Visitors can explore several themed areas including:
            </p>

            <ul>
                <li>Ocean Giants Zone</li>
                <li>Coral Reef Discovery</li>
                <li>Tropical Rainforest Habitat</li>
                <li>Deep Sea Exploration</li>
                <li>Arctic Marine Life</li>
            </ul>
        </div>


        <div class="faq-item">
            <h2>Is Aquarium World suitable for children?</h2>
            <p>
                Yes. Aquarium World provides interactive exhibits,
                educational activities, and family-friendly experiences
                designed for visitors of all ages.
            </p>
        </div>


        <div class="faq-item">
            <h2>Is the aquarium accessible for visitors with disabilities?</h2>
            <p>
                Yes. The aquarium provides wheelchair-accessible routes,
                accessible toilets, and assistance for visitors who require
                additional support.
            </p>
        </div>


        <div class="faq-item">
            <h2>Can I take photographs inside the aquarium?</h2>
            <p>
                Photography is allowed in most areas for personal use.
                Flash photography is restricted because it may disturb
                marine animals.
            </p>
        </div>


        <div class="faq-item">
            <h2>How does Aquarium World support conservation?</h2>
            <p>
                Aquarium World supports marine conservation through habitat
                protection projects, research programs, animal welfare
                initiatives, and public education.
            </p>
        </div>


        <div class="faq-item">
            <h2>Are food and drinks available inside the aquarium?</h2>
            <p>
                Yes. Visitors can enjoy refreshments at our café.
                Food and drinks are only permitted in designated areas.
            </p>
        </div>

    </section>


    <section class="faq-contact">
        <h2>Still have questions?</h2>
        <p>
            Contact our visitor support team for further information.
        </p>

        <a href="/contact" class="btn">
            Contact Us
        </a>
    </section>

</main>


<%- include("partials/footer") %>